      • Serialized Fields

        • pop

          Population pop
          The Population to which this Animal and all other Animals that it can know about belong.

        • gInfo

          GenomeInfo gInfo
          The GenomeInfo that is used in creating this individual's Genome and determine its genotypes.
          This is the same for all animals in the same Population.

        • pgInfo

          PseudoGenomeInfo pgInfo
          The PseudoGenomeInfo that is used in creating this individual's Genome and determine its genotypes.
          This is the same for all animals in the same Population.

        • sex

          int sex
          Tag used to establish an individual's sex.
          Values are compared with those in Defaults
          Currently only two sexes are supported. This could be changed but would require much name changing and some storage changes as well.

        • birthCycle

          int birthCycle
          The "year" in which this animal was born.
          Negative numbers are used if this animal is a founder and is more than 0 years old.

        • numProgeny

          int numProgeny
          The number of animals that can claim this as a parent. This is incremented via Animal.addOffspring(edu.iastate.ansci.flip.Animal) so that one might separate natural offspring from AI or other offspring if desired.

        • idNum

          java.lang.Long idNum
          The identification number for this animal. It is stored as a Long, so the program is "limited" to 2^63-1 animals. The numbers are incremented for each new animal created in a given population starting from 0.

        • damID

          java.lang.Long damID
          The identification number for this animal's genetic "mother". A -1 is assigned if this animal is a founder since its parents do not belong to this population. The "mother" is the homogametic parent which would be the male in birds.

        • sireID

          java.lang.Long sireID
          The identification number for this animal's genetic "father". A -1 is assigned if this animal is a founder since its parents do not belong to this population. The "father" is the heterogametic parent which would be the female in birds.

        • clonedFrom

          java.lang.Long clonedFrom
          The identification number of the animal for which this animal is a clone. A -1 designates that this animal is not a clone.
          A clone is an animal with identical Animal.genome and Animal.pGenome but potentially different Animal.phenotypes do to differing environments.

        • surrogateID

          java.lang.Long surrogateID
          The identification number for the animal that serves as the maternal environment for pre/post birth traits for clones and/or embryo transfers. A -1 is assigned for natural matings.

        • genotypes

          java.util.HashMap<K,V> genotypes
          The values of this animal's individual allele combination for the GenotypeInfos specified in Animal.genome.

        • sourceHerd

          Herd sourceHerd
          The Herd in which this animal originated

        • breedComposition

          double[] breedComposition
          Stores the fractional amounts of each breed that this animal represents

        • alive

          int[] alive
          An array which has been sized to the maximum age for this species that states whether or not this animal survived to a specified age. For example: if the maximum age is 5, then {T,T,T,F,F} implies that this animal died after 3 cycles.

        • numberFertilized

          int[] numberFertilized
          The number of eggs fertilized by this animal for each cycle of its life. This does not imply that all of the fertilized eggs were born alive.

        • numberBorn

          int[] numberBorn
          The number of animals the were born to this animal for each cycle of its life. Some of the offspring may have died before actually being born.

        • numberBornAlive

          int[] numberBornAlive
          The number of animals that survived the birthing process for each cycle of this animals life.

        • genome

          Genome genome
          The Genome of this animal containing the alleles for this individual's "known" loci.

        • pGenome

          PseudoGenome pGenome
          The PseudoGenome of this animal containing the alleles for this individual's "unknown" loci.

        • justCreated

          boolean justCreated
          Flag set when an animal is created to distinguish founders with nonzero ages from those that were created in previous cycles.

        • genesLoaded

          boolean genesLoaded
          Flag used to determine if genes need to be read from a file when requested.

          Used for displaying/modifying the covariances of the pseudoGenome. To be used, this table must not be singular. Changes to this table result in changes to the overall covariances as displayed in CovariancePane.requestsTable

          javax.swing.JSpinner dominanceLevel
          Used to display/modify the amount of dominance in the "variance" pseudo genes. These "genes" have 2 alleles with frequencies of .5 each and effects of +a and -a. So with the default of no dominance, their means are 0. By adding some dominance, one could account for some of the desired mean level.
